---

## RTL Schematic

The schematic below was generated using **Xilinx Vivado** after synthesis. It shows the design mapped to a **SLICEM** primitive (`SLICE_X14Y123`) using internal carry logic and LUT-based outputs.

![!RTL schematic](Decoder2to4_schmatic.png)]

### Schematic Explanation

The synthesized design uses a single **SLICEM** (Slice with Memory capability) on the FPGA fabric:

- **S0–S3** — Select/input lines mapped from `A(1:0)` and `EN`
- **DI0–DI3** — Data inputs feeding into the LUT logic
- **O0–O3** — Output lines corresponding to `Y(0)` through `Y(3)`
- **CO0–CO3** — Carry-out lines used internally by the slice
- **CIN / CYINIT** — Carry-in initialization for the carry chain
- **O0 (CYINIT path)** — Handles the base carry initialization

The decoder logic is efficiently packed into a **single FPGA slice**, demonstrating minimal resource utilization.

---

## VHDL Source

### decoder_2to4.vhd

```vhdl
library IEEE;
use IEEE.STD_LOGIC_1164.ALL;

entity decoder_2to4 is
    Port (
        A  : in  STD_LOGIC_VECTOR(1 downto 0);
        EN : in  STD_LOGIC;
        Y  : out STD_LOGIC_VECTOR(3 downto 0)
    );
end decoder_2to4;

architecture Behavioral of decoder_2to4 is
begin
    process(A, EN)
    begin
        if EN = '1' then
            case A is
                when "00"   => Y <= "0001";
                when "01"   => Y <= "0010";
                when "10"   => Y <= "0100";
                when "11"   => Y <= "1000";
                when others => Y <= "0000";
            end case;
        else
            Y <= "0000";
        end if;
    end process;
end Behavioral;
```

